question: A maintenance worker has to clean a university with 105 rooms. They have 5 days to get it done. It takes them 10 minutes per room. If they work 13 hours each day, what percentage of their day, on average, is spent cleaning rooms?
answer:
They have to clean 21 rooms a day because 105 / 5 = <<105/5=21>>21
They spend 210 minutes cleaning per day because 21*10 = <<21*10=210>>210
They spend 3.5 hours a day because 210 / 60 = <<210/60=3.5>>3.5
They spend 7/26 of their day cleaning rooms because 3.5 / 13 = <<3.5/13=0.2692307692307692>>0.2692307692307692
They spend 26% of their day cleaning rooms because 0.2692307692307692*100 = <<0.2692307692307692*100=26>>26
#### 26
